# antd-style Patterns

## styles.ts Pattern
Every component has a `styles.ts` using `createStyles`:

```typescript
import { createStyles } from 'antd-style';

const useStyles = createStyles(({ css }) => {
    return css({
        '&.component-name': {
            display: 'flex',
            '.component-name-childElement': {
                fontSize: 14
            }
        }
    });
});

export default useStyles;
```

## Usage in Components
```typescript
const { styles, cx } = useStyles();

// Root element — injects generated CSS
<div className={cx('component-name', styles.toString())}>
    {/* Children — plain string matching CSS rule */}
    <span className={'component-name-childElement'}>Text</span>
</div>
```

## Rules
- Root: `className={cx('kebab-case-name', styles.toString())}`
- Children: `className={'component-name-child'}` (plain string)
- Conditional: `cx('class-a', condition && 'class-b')`
- Theme tokens: use `token` from `createStyles(({ css, token }) => ...)`
- Animations: use `keyframes` from `antd-style`, not CSS `@keyframes`
- `index.css` — only global styles (fonts, reset, scrollbar)
